\date{2025-02-22}
\title{limits of regular languages are deterministic B端chi recognizable}
\author{trebor}
\import{common}
\taxon{theorem}

\p{
  Given a regular language #{\mathcal{L}}, its [limit](misc-000H) #{\lim \mathcal{L}} can be recognized by a deterministic B端chi automaton, by simply regarding a DFA for #{\mathcal{L}} as a B端chi automaton. In fact, every deterministic B端chi recognizable #{\omega}-language is of this form.
}
